# GeoNames EU slice v3 — benchmark-grade, trimmed
#
# 15 concepts, four-level hierarchy, all real GeoNames IDs verified against
# sws.geonames.org and admin1CodesASCII.txt.
#
# Structure:
#   Europe (L.CONT)
#   +-- France (A.PCLI)
#   |   +-- 6 ADM1 regions: Ile-de-France, Grand Est, PACA, Occitanie,
#   |   |   Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes, Nouvelle-Aquitaine
#   |   +-- 2 cities: Paris (under Ile-de-France),
#   |                 Strasbourg (under Grand Est)
#   +-- Germany (A.PCLI)
#       +-- 3 Bundeslaender: Bayern, Berlin (Land), Baden-Wuerttemberg
#       +-- 1 city: Munich (under Bayern)
#
# Rationale: ADM1 breadth drives sibling-disjointness test cases (RQ2).
# Cities are anchor points for `eq X` constraints; three is enough:
#   - Paris: continent -> country -> region -> city chain (deep case)
#   - Strasbourg: motivating example from the paper
#   - Munich: cross-country case (isPartOf France vs eq Munich)
#
# Predicate shape mirrors live GeoNames RDF: parentFeature is the immediate
# parent; parentCountry and parentADM1 provide shortcut edges.
#
# No disjointness is asserted. This matches real GeoNames and keeps the
# baseline honest: the SDA profile is applied at evaluation time.

@prefix gn:   <https://www.geonames.org/ontology#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

### Continent ###############################################################

<https://sws.geonames.org/6255148/> a gn:Feature ;
    gn:name "Europe" ;
    gn:featureCode gn:L.CONT .

### Countries (A.PCLI) ######################################################

<https://sws.geonames.org/3017382/> a gn:Feature ;
    gn:name "France" ;
    gn:featureCode gn:A.PCLI ;
    gn:countryCode "FR" ;
    gn:parentFeature <https://sws.geonames.org/6255148/> .

<https://sws.geonames.org/2921044/> a gn:Feature ;
    gn:name "Germany" ;
    gn:featureCode gn:A.PCLI ;
    gn:countryCode "DE" ;
    gn:parentFeature <https://sws.geonames.org/6255148/> .

